"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 08, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ifd1665702744188.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ifd1665702744188.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ifd1665702744188.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ifd1665702744188\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n           \n Configuring the Uniface IDE\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">You can configure the Uniface IDE using the <span class=\"ph filepath\">ide.asn</span> and <span class=\"ph filepath\">usys.ini</span> files.\n </p>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step\" id=\"ifd1665702744188__li_d15386e1_d15387e1_d15388e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">If you use a database other than SQLite as the Repository, edit the <span class=\"ph filepath\">dbms.asn</span> file to configure the database connector for your database. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qpp1665702522210.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qpp1665702522210.html\" title=\"You can configure Uniface to access any supported database for the Repository or application data.\">Configuring the Database Connector</a>.\n            </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"ifd1665702744188__li_d15389e1_d15390e1_d15391e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"ifd1665702744188__p_d30431e1_d30432e1_d30433e1\">Optionally, configure the location of application objects during development using the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$RESOURCES_OUTPUT</span> setting.\n The application file locations established here can also be used to set up the resource locations in the deployed application.</span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"ifd1665702744188__li_d15392e1_d15393e1_d15394e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Set script editor preferences and default templates in the\n                  <span class=\"ph filepath\">ide.asn</span>.For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fen1702546666129.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fen1702546666129.html\" title=\"You can configure the behavior of the Uniface IDE by setting preferences in the IDE assignment and initialization files.\">Set Uniface IDE Preferences</a>. </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"ifd1665702744188__li_d15395e1_d15396e1_d15397e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"ifd1665702744188__p_d30434e1_d30435e1_d30436e1\">Optionally, set up your own environment for\n               developing applications, including a program group, customized assignment files, and\n               shortcuts that include command line switches and parameters customized for your\n               environment. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"hxc1665702744973.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hxc1665702744973.html\" title=\"Uniface provides a command line interface that enables you to access many functions without actually opening the user interface. By running a Uniface executable (such as ide.exe or uniface) with command line switches you can compile objects, debug applications, import and export, specify assignment files, and more.\">Uniface Command Line Interface</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"asd1665702742243.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/asd1665702742243.html\" title=\"Uniface configuration files include assignment files, initialization files, and web application files.\">Configuration Files</a>. </span>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zhr1665702742172.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Configuring Uniface and Uniface Applications</a><p>Deploying a Uniface enterprise application is largely a matter of configuring the environment to ensure that all components are running in the appropriate locations and that Uniface is able to find them. Configuration files ensure that the Uniface runtime environment can locate and initialize the application components correctly.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fen1702546666129.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Set Uniface IDE Preferences</a><p>You can configure the behavior of the Uniface IDE by setting preferences in the IDE assignment and initialization files.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528517\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528517\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Configuring the Uniface IDE Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 08, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Configuring the Uniface IDE You can configure the Uniface IDE using the ide.asn and usys.ini files. If you use a database other than SQLite as the Repository, edit the dbms.asn file to configure the database connector for your database. For more information, see Configuring the Database Connector . Optionally, configure the location of application objects during development using the $RESOURCES_OUTPUT setting. The application file locations established here can also be used to set up the resource locations in the deployed application. Set script editor preferences and default templates in the ide.asn .For more information, see Set Uniface IDE Preferences . Optionally, set up your own environment for developing applications, including a program group, customized assignment files, and shortcuts that include command line switches and parameters customized for your environment. For more information, see Uniface Command Line Interface and Configuration Files . Related Links Configuring Uniface and Uniface Applications Deploying a Uniface enterprise application is largely a matter of configuring the environment to ensure that all components are running in the appropriate locations and that Uniface is able to find them. Configuration files ensure that the Uniface runtime environment can locate and initialize the application components correctly. Set Uniface IDE Preferences You can configure the behavior of the Uniface IDE by setting preferences in the IDE assignment and initialization files. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}